metadata.name: Burnout
metadata.description:
What do you feel looking at this?
What emotions does it evoke?
Anxiety, fear, tantrum, shame? etc.

They say: it's impossible to run away from yourself. Yes you can't, but it's possible to lose yourself.  

I tell myself every time I want to run away from myself:
There are no bad and good emotions. They're all yours. Do not divide yourself into black and white. All you feel is you. Let all the emotions live. And that's the only way you won't lose yourself and burn out. 

(5480 x 6345; PNG; 29 Mb)
